            <title>[LOG4J2-3289] log4j-to-slf4j should not re-format the result of Message.getFormattedMessage</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-3289</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Both the formatted message result (for the configured MessageFactory) and the parameter array are passed to slf4j, such that slf4j attempts to format the already formatted result:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/blob/20f9a97dbe5928c3b5077bcdd2a22ac92e941655/log4j-to-slf4j/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/slf4j/SLF4JLogger.java#L226-L256&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/blob/20f9a97dbe5928c3b5077bcdd2a22ac92e941655/log4j-to-slf4j/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/slf4j/SLF4JLogger.java#L226-L256&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Caught a similar issue while reviewing this change, but realized it also applies to the slf4j bridge:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/653#discussion_r775083351&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/653#discussion_r775083351&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
